Building:

mkdir tmp
cd tmp
cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr ..
make
sudo make install

Or to manually install it, copy src/screenshot and src/imageshack.us.py files to /usr/bin or other bin directory from $PATH,
copy imageshack.us.desktop to /usr/share/kde4/services/ServiceMenus/ or to ~/.kde/share/kde4/services/ServiceMenus/
And satisfy depensies: scrot, xlip, notify-send (or kde-base-apps-bin).

For Debian and Ubuntu You can build a deb package with cpack or standard Debian way.